statements: SELECT * FROM MentorshipProgram;
SELECT mentor_name, mentor_email FROM MentorshipProgram;
SELECT mentor_name, mentor_interests FROM MentorshipProgram WHERE mentor_id = 1;
SELECT mentor_name, mentor_email, mentor_interests FROM MentorshipProgram WHERE mentor_skills LIKE '%programming%';
SELECT * FROM MentorshipProgram WHERE mentor_id IN (2, 4, 6);
SELECT mentor_name, mentor_email FROM MentorshipProgram WHERE mentor_id = 1;
SELECT mentor_name, mentor_skills FROM MentorshipProgram WHERE mentor_interests LIKE '%programming%';
SELECT * FROM MentorshipProgram WHERE mentor_id IN (1, 3, 5);
SELECT mentor_email, mentor_interests, mentor_skills FROM MentorshipProgram ORDER BY mentor_name DESC;
SELECT mentor_name, mentor_interests FROM MentorshipProgram WHERE mentor_skills IS NOT NULL AND mentor_skills != '';
SELECT * FROM mentors WHERE name = 'John';
SELECT id, name FROM mentors WHERE interests = 'Programming';
SELECT email FROM mentees WHERE interests = 'Data Science' ORDER BY email DESC;
SELECT * FROM mentees WHERE id = 2;
SELECT name, email FROM mentors WHERE interests = 'AI' ORDER BY name ASC;
SELECT * FROM mentors WHERE interests='Programming' ORDER BY name DESC;
SELECT id, name, email FROM mentors WHERE email LIKE '%@gmail.com' AND interests='Data Science';
SELECT name, interests FROM mentors WHERE interests IN ('Programming', 'Database Management') ORDER BY id ASC;
SELECT * FROM mentees WHERE interests='Artificial Intelligence' AND name LIKE '%John%' ORDER BY id DESC;
SELECT id, name FROM mentees WHERE interests='Machine Learning' AND email='john.doe@example.com';
SELECT * FROM Mentors;
SELECT mentor_name, mentor_experience_years FROM Mentors ORDER BY mentor_experience_years DESC;
SELECT mentee_name, mentee_interests FROM Mentees WHERE mentee_experience_years > 2;
SELECT mentor_name, mentor_id, mentor_experience_years FROM Mentors WHERE mentor_experience_years >= 5;
SELECT mentee_name, mentor_preferences FROM Mentees ORDER BY mentee_name ASC;
SELECT mentor_name, mentor_experience_years FROM Mentors ORDER BY mentor_experience_years DESC LIMIT 3;
SELECT mentee_name, mentee_experience_years FROM Mentees WHERE mentee_experience_years >= 2 ORDER BY mentee_name ASC;

SELECT m.mentor_name, me.mentee_name, mm.match_score FROM Mentors m JOIN MentorshipMatches mm ON m.mentor_id = mm.mentor_id JOIN Mentees me ON mm.mentee_id = me.mentee_id WHERE mm.match_score > 0.8 ORDER BY mm.match_score DESC LIMIT 5;
SELECT mentor_name, mentor_interests, mentor_experience_years FROM Mentors WHERE mentor_experience_years > 5 ORDER BY mentor_name ASC;
SELECT mentee_name, mentee_interests, mentor_preferences FROM Mentees WHERE mentor_preferences IS NOT NULL ORDER BY mentee_name DESC LIMIT 3;
SELECT * FROM Mentors;
SELECT mentor_name, expertise_area FROM Mentors WHERE mentor_id = 1;
SELECT mentor_name, availability FROM Mentors WHERE expertise_area = 'Technology';
SELECT mentee_name, interests FROM Mentees WHERE level_of_experience = 'Intermediate';

SELECT mentor_name, mentee_name, match_date FROM Mentors INNER JOIN MentorshipMatches ON Mentors.mentor_id = MentorshipMatches.mentor_id INNER JOIN Mentees ON MentorshipMatches.mentee_id = Mentees.mentee_id;
SELECT * FROM Mentors WHERE mentor_id = 1;
SELECT mentor_name, expertise_area FROM Mentors WHERE availability > '2022-01-01';
SELECT m.mentor_name, s.compatibility_score FROM Mentors m JOIN CompatibilityScores s ON m.mentor_id = s.mentor_id WHERE s.compatibility_score > 80;
SELECT m.mentor_name, e.interests FROM Mentors m JOIN Mentees e ON m.expertise_area = e.interests;

SELECT m.mentor_name, e.mentee_name, c.compatibility_score FROM Mentors m JOIN MentorshipMatches mm ON m.mentor_id = mm.mentor_id JOIN Mentees e ON mm.mentee_id = e.mentee_id JOIN CompatibilityScores c ON m.mentor_id = c.mentor_id WHERE mm.match_date >= '2022-10-01';
SELECT * FROM mentors;
SELECT mentor_id, mentor_name FROM mentors WHERE mentor_exp > 5;
SELECT mentee_name, mentee_interests FROM mentees ORDER BY mentee_exp DESC;
SELECT mentor_name, COUNT(mentor_id) FROM mentors INNER JOIN mentor_interests ON mentors.mentor_id = mentor_interests.mentor_id GROUP BY mentor_name;
SELECT mentor_name, mentee_name, score FROM mentors JOIN compatibility ON mentors.mentor_id = compatibility.mentor_id JOIN mentees ON mentees.mentee_id = compatibility.mentee_id WHERE score > 75;
SELECT * FROM mentors ORDER BY mentor_exp DESC, mentor_name
SELECT mentor_name, mentor_interests FROM mentors WHERE mentor_exp > 5
SELECT mentor_name, m.mentor_exp, i.interest_name FROM mentors m JOIN mentor_interests mi ON m.mentor_id = mi.mentor_id JOIN interests i ON mi.interest_id = i.interest_id
SELECT mentor_name, COUNT(mentor_interests) AS num_interests FROM mentors GROUP BY mentor_name HAVING num_interests > 2
SELECT m.mentor_name, me.mentee_name, c.score FROM mentors m JOIN compatibility c ON m.mentor_id = c.mentor_id JOIN mentees me ON c.mentee_id = me.mentee_id WHERE c.score > 80
